<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="868" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Nabeshima</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-01"><hi rend="italic">June 1,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 38.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 30th ultimo, protesting against the alleged
                            discrimination against <pb facs="0843" n="745" xml:id="pg_745"/>
                            Japanese subjects in San Francisco in the enforcement of the measures
                            adopted to prevent the spread of bubonic plague.</p>
                        <p>In reply, I beg to inform you that a copy of your note has been sent to
                            the Secretary of theTreasuiy for his information and consideration.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>